V.42bis tests

What does it do?

These tests compress the contents of a file specified on the command line, writing the compressed data to v42bis_tests.v42bis. They then read back the contents of the compressed file, decompress, and write the results to v42bis_tests.out. The contents of this file should exactly match the original file.
